The Kano Electricity Distribution Company said it will inaugurate a taskforce tribunal to prosecute energy theft, meter bypass offenders, among others in its franchise states comprising Jigawa, Kano and Katsina. The spokesman, Ibrahim Sani Shawai, who disclosed this in a statement yesterday said, “The task force tribunal which is to investigate and prosecute cases of energy theft, meter by-pass and associated offences for the Kano Electricity Distribution Company (KEDCO) will soon be inaugurated.” The DisCo said the taskforce team which has already arrived Kano was set up by the Director of Public Prosecution of the Federation. The main activities will be to strictly prosecute after investigation, all cases of energy theft and related offences that are perpetuated to cause any economic loss to KEDCO. It noted that similar tribunal has been operating in other DisCos’ franchise area and that it was now time for Kano and Kaduna DisCos. Kano Disco commissions substation in Farawa Kano DisCo laments energy theft, night connections We’re investing on maintenance, network expansion - Kano DisCo OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY